body:
**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**
It's nither feature nor a bug

**What is the current behavior?**
When I use useEffect for including styles onto a page (with style-loader/usable) - page is flickering.
Such behaviour have not been seen when I used injecting styles in ComponentWillMount handler

**What is the expected behavior?**
Render a page without visual flickering content

**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**

React - 16.7.0-alpha.0
browser - any
OS - any

Declare hook
```js
import { useEffect } from 'react';

const useStyles = css => {
    useEffect(() => {
        css.forEach(item => item.use());

        return () => css.forEach(item => item.unuse());
    }, []);

    return css.reduce((acc: object, item) => (acc = Object.assign({}, acc, item.locals)), {}) as any;
};

export default useStyles;
```
Using hook
```js
import React from 'react';
import useStyles from '../hooks/useStyles';

import AppLayout from '../components/AppLayout';

import appCSS from './app.css';

const App = () => {
    useStyles([appCSS]);

    return <AppLayout />;
};

export default App;
```
rendering is going from the deepest component in component tree - so the styles begin applying after rendering the whole component tree.

Using 
```js
componentWillMount() {
   css.use();
}
```
did not lead to such deffects
